result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeremy A Heisel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Armed Robbery, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 3:19 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Mac J. Davis presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Jeremy A Heisel in court, in-custody, with Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek. ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent.  
Mr. Heisel waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
State files information; Arraignment:--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "Guilty" entered on Counts #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds the Defendant  guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #3

On Count #1, the Court sentences Mr. Heisel to 8 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 4 years and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 4 years. This sentence is to commence consecutive to sentence currently in being
On Count #2, the Court sentences Mr. Heisel to 3 years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 1 year and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 2 years.  This sentence is to commence consecutive to Count #1
 
The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and the Substance Abuse Program. 
The Court gives 0 days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--No Contact with Bajwa Gas Station otherwise known as the Clark Gas Station in Watertown
--No Contact with the owners of the Clark Gas Station
--Absolute sobriety
--To pay restitution of $300
--To pay 10% restitution surcharge
--To pay costs/fees of this action, including DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Surcharge
--To comply with random drug screens as requested by DOC

Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant
